.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:199:2. Reserve one coordinator to maintain the verdict table and prompt-equality audit.
.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:253:Prompt: `Review the staged one-file diff findings-first, with file:line evidence for P0/P1 issues and a clear merge posture.`
.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:269:Prompt: `Review the full refactor branch diff, call out large-diff limits and surface evidence, and keep blockers severity-ordered.`
.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:285:Prompt: `Review the branch from merge-base to HEAD, preserving commit lineage and flagging unrelated-change risk.`
.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:307:Prompt: `Review this auth-sensitive diff for missing auth or ownership checks, treating likely authorization gaps as P1/P0 risks.`
.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:323:Prompt: `Review this validation diff for injection risks, tracing untrusted input to SQL, command, path, SSRF, or HTML sinks.`
.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:339:Prompt: `Scan the staged diff for hardcoded credentials, private keys, passwords, tokens, and sensitive logs without echoing real secrets.`
.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:361:Prompt: `Validate this suspected P0 diff hunk with exact file:line evidence, user impact, finding class, and an evidence-backed severity.`
