.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/specific/manual_testing_playbook_creation.md:113:2. `## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT`
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/specific/manual_testing_playbook_creation.md:148:### When to Use RCAF vs Natural-Human
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/specific/manual_testing_playbook_creation.md:150:The canonical Prompt: field defaults to **natural-human voice**. Match how a real user would phrase the request to an AI in conversation. Use the RCAF (Role-Context-Action-Format) wrapper "As a {ROLE}, {ACTION} against {TARGET}. Verify {EXPECTED_OUTCOME}. Return {OUTPUT_FORMAT}." **only** when the actor IS an AI orchestrator.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/specific/manual_testing_playbook_creation.md:152:| Use **natural-human** when… | Use **RCAF** when… |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/specific/manual_testing_playbook_creation.md:159:**When in doubt: prefer natural-human.** RCAF is the exception, natural is the default.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/specific/manual_testing_playbook_creation.md:167:**Voice guidelines for RCAF when retained**:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/specific/manual_testing_playbook_creation.md:171:The `Real user request:` field is always natural-human regardless of which voice the canonical Prompt: field uses; it serves as the voice reference baseline.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/specific/manual_testing_playbook_creation.md:174:- the structured prompt field in `SCENARIO CONTRACT`
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/specific/manual_testing_playbook_creation.md:175:- the `Exact Prompt` column in the execution table
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/specific/manual_testing_playbook_creation.md:230:| Unsynced prompt fields | Operators do not know which prompt is canonical | Update `SCENARIO CONTRACT`, table prompt and root summary together |
