.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:859:Prompt: `Validate observer-effect mitigation and cite whether search still works when eval logging fails without adding latency.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:873:Prompt: `Validate the quality proxy formula and cite whether the stored value matches manual calculation with all components present.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:887:Prompt: `Validate the synthetic ground-truth corpus and cite coverage for intents, hard negatives, non-trigger prompts, and tier balance.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:901:Prompt: `Validate the BM25-only baseline and cite whether ENABLE_BM25 produces reproducible MRR@5 with no non-BM25 trace contributions.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:915:Prompt: `Validate agent consumption instrumentation and cite whether the logger gate stays inert while telemetry handlers remain error-free.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:929:Prompt: `Validate scoring observability and cite whether sampled rows are logged, sample rate is respected, and write failures do not crash search.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:943:Prompt: `Validate reporting and ablation output and cite whether each channel has deltas, dashboard trends, and no empty reports.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:957:Prompt: `Validate typed-weighted degree scoring and cite caps, batched cold-cache queries, cache reuse, fallback, and varied type scoring.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:971:Prompt: `Validate co-activation boost strength and cite contribution delta, batched hydration, causal-neighbor query shape, and one precompute per batch.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:985:Prompt: `Validate edge density measurement and cite whether edges/nodes ratio and threshold gate behavior are correct.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:999:Prompt: `Validate weight history audit tracking and cite audit rows, rollback restoration, and append-only history evidence.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1013:Prompt: `Validate graph momentum scoring and cite capped 7-day momentum bonus plus zero bonus for nodes without history.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1027:Prompt: `Validate causal depth scoring and cite normalization, longer-chain ranking, shortcut behavior, and cycle depth bounding.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1041:Prompt: `Validate community detection and cite cluster assignment, co-member boost injection, and configured boost cap enforcement.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1055:Prompt: `Validate Score normalization with range, min-max, equal-score, and single-result evidence.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1069:Prompt: `Confirm N4 novelty hot-path removal. Capture the evidence needed to prove Novelty boost contribution is zero in telemetry; code path shows novelty removed from hot scoring path. Return a concise user-facing pass/fail verdict with the main reason.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1083:Prompt: `Validate interference scoring penalties for near duplicates, non-duplicates, and inactive or deprecated siblings.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1097:Prompt: `Validate classification-based decay, including tier multipliers and rejection of zero half-life config.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1111:Prompt: `Validate folder-level relevance scoring and confirm folder results rank before individual memory results.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1125:Prompt: `Validate embedding cache hits, misses, and hit timestamp updates.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1139:Prompt: `Validate double intent weighting handling for hybrid and non-hybrid queries.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1153:Prompt: `Validate RRF K-value sensitivity analysis and identify the optimal K with evidence.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1167:Prompt: `Validate the negative feedback confidence signal, including floor enforcement and half-life recovery.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1181:Prompt: `Validate auto-promotion on validation, including threshold promotion, throttle behavior, and audit logging.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1195:Prompt: `As a query-intelligence validation operator, validate Query complexity router (R15) against the documented validation surface. Verify simple queries route to fewer channels; complex queries activate all channels; disabled flag falls back to default routing. Return a concise pass/fail verdict with the main reason and cited evidence.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1209:Prompt: `N/A — active manual validation for RSF live ranking was removed from the playbook because production ranking stays on RRF and RSF is no longer a shipped runtime path.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1223:Prompt: `As a query-intelligence validation operator, validate Channel min-representation (R2) against the documented validation surface. Verify each channel represented in top-k results even when one channel dominates; quality floor prevents low-relevance injection. Return a concise pass/fail verdict with the main reason and cited evidence.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1237:Prompt: `As a query-intelligence validation operator, validate Confidence-based result truncation (R15-ext) against the documented validation surface. Verify results truncated at confidence cliff; minimum result count guaranteed; cutoff threshold documented in trace. Return a concise pass/fail verdict with the main reason and cited evidence.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1251:Prompt: `As a query-intelligence validation operator, validate Dynamic token budget allocation (FUT-7) against the documented validation surface. Verify token budget scales with query complexity tier; simple queries get smaller budgets; disabled flag falls back to default budget. Return a concise pass/fail verdict with the main reason and cited evidence.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1265:Prompt: `As a query-intelligence validation operator, validate Query expansion (R12) against the documented validation surface. Verify complex queries produce expanded variants; expanded results deduplicated against baseline; simple queries skip expansion. Return a concise pass/fail verdict with the main reason and cited evidence.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1279:Prompt: `Validate the verify-fix-verify memory quality loop.`
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:1293:Prompt: `Validate signal vocabulary expansion for correction, preference, and reinforcement signals.`
